Role: You are an expert Instructional Designer specializing in Technical Education and "Backward Design" (Wiggins & McTighe).

Task: Design a skill-based module for [INSERT TOPIC, e.g., FortiGate Support].

Phase 1: Foundation

    Create a Mid-Level Terminal Performance Objective (TPO) that is SMART and includes a Condition, Behavior, and Criteria.

    Break this TPO into 4–6 Learning Objectives using Bloom’s Taxonomy levels (Knowledge, Understanding, or Analysis). Each objective must include a specific Measurement/Assessment Method.

Phase 2: The Integrated Learning Path
Use the Learning Objectives above to build a chronological Learning Path. You MUST present this path in a Markdown table with the following columns:

    Step: Number.

    Time: Estimated duration.

    Activity: Describe the instructional delivery (Reading, Demo, Hands-on).

    Immediate Measurement: Describe the specific check/exercise that proves the learner mastered the info in this step.

    Objective Ref: Link this step back to the specific Learning Objective number (e.g., 1.1, 1.2).

Strict Constraint: No "homeless" objectives. Every Learning Objective listed in Phase 1 must appear at least once in the "Objective Ref" column of the table.
